. Sure she had to get captured and put in the white tower to do it but finally her story arc is way more interesting.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e✔ - Nynaeve and Lan finally getting a little relationship fleshing out and one of my favorite moments of the series. Way to go all Aes Sedea on your man Nynaeve. This is probably the only time I will approve of such a move.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e✔ - Avienda cutting strings from Elayne. Maybe it will be her turn with Rand again soon.\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e✔ - Rand outing another of the Forsaken. The price might be a little heavy but he just keeps on swimming. Actually I love him and Min together, she seems to get him better than anyone else and I love how in her own way she is just as strong or actually stronger than him. \u003cinput type=\"checkbox\" class=\"spoiler__control\" aria-label=\"The following text has been marked spoiler. Toggle checkbox to reveal or hide.\" onchange=\"this.labels[0].setAttribute('aria-hidden', !this.checked);\" id=\"855757b3-3a71-4e1b-a4e0-9bf90e8da89f\" /\u003e\u003clabel aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"spoiler\" for=\"855757b3-3a71-4e1b-a4e0-9bf90e8da89f\"\u003edo we need those other women at all….I think not. Actually I think Avienda and Elayne should just do their own thing they don’t seem to need Rand at all\u003c/label\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e✔ - Mat and Tuon playing courting games that seem more like battle strategy \u003cb\u003eI LOVE THEM SO MUCH TOGETHER\u003c/b\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e✔ - Thom finally telling us what is in that letter that Moraince left for him how many books ago. Well we get to read it \u003cb\u003eAND\u003c/b\u003e I’m so excited about where that is going to lead our crew. \u003cbr\u003e\u003cbr\u003e✔ - The Elayne the Daughter Heir finally finding her place. Whether it is on the Lion throne or not you will just have to read to see. Her arc is actually my least favorite maybe because so much time is spent on the pregnancy and sometimes she i